      {
        "id": 2323414,
        "name": "Gerhard P.  (P r @ \u20ac s e n t)",
        "username": "Gerhard_P",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-25T10:59:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Ian Sutton\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Ian Sutton:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We\u2019re planning to pop over to France sometime soon, and part of the trip will be to pick up some Pomerol for the brains of the operation. Looking back at CT, these appear to have gone down well previously:<br>\n1981 Vieux Chateau Certan<br>\n1981 Clos du Clocher<br>\n1994 La Pointe<br>\n1995 La Croix du Casse<br>\n1995 La Croix du Gay<br>\n1999 La Rose Figeac<br>\n2000 La Grave a Pomerol (this more voluptuous than we\u2019d normally seek, but enjoyed it nonetheless)<br>\n2009 La Croix du Gay</p>\n<p>Definitely playing at the low-middle end of the pricing scale (e.g. VCC is way too pricey for us these days) and definitely wanting to avoid excess of oak and alcohol (and overly rich/ripe fruit).</p>\n<p>Any thoughts of more modest producers worth a try? Likely to be we\u2019ll end up with a number of single bottles, though some of the above might tempt us to 2-3 bottles.</p>\n<p>In terms of vintages, I see 2009/2010 &amp; 2015/6 touted, but 2012 worth considering as well?</p>\n<p>Regards<br>\nIan</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>FWIW - I had the 1981 Vieux Chateau Certan<br>\nin October \u2026 it was good, however fully mature (if not slightly over apogee) a more intellectual wine than for pure hedonistic pleasure, nose complex but a bit medicinal, palate quite dry, acidity coming through, very tertiaer \u2026 medium length, lacking a bit of ripe fruit \u2026<br>\n(ok, but I wouldn\u00b4t buy it again now)</p>\n<p>I don\u00b4t think the 1981 Clos du Clocher<br>\nwill be any better, if not definitely weaker \u2026</p>\n<p>1994 La Pointe<br>\n(possible if low priced, but I guess far from great)</p>\n<p>These two:<br>\n1995 La Croix du Casse<br>\n1995 La Croix du Gay<br>\ncould be quite good if in good shape \u2026</p>\n<p>1999 La Rose Figeac<br>\n(a small wine)</p>\n<p>2000 La Grave a Pomerol<br>\n2009 La Croix de Gay<br>\n(especially the latter quite young and modern)</p>\n<p>If available (and affordable) you might also try:<br>\nGazin (I had a stunning 1992 (!) last week \u2026 after 5 hours slow-oxing \u2026<br>\nL\u00b4Enclos can be good (1990 !)<br>\nLatour a Pomerol<br>\nPetit Village<br>\nDomaine de l\u00b4Eglise (1989 !)<br>\nRouget<br>\n(not talking about the best producers like L\u00b4Evangile, Conseillante \u2026)</p>\n<p>2012 is a very good but not great vintage, IMHO better than 2011 and 2013(!) \u2026 however quite young now \u2026</p>",
